info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Statement issued November 09 at 4:05AM EST until November 09 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT... * WHAT...Minor saltwater flooding. * WHERE...Middle Keys, especially near times of high tide. * WHEN...Through late this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Minor saltwater flooding of low elevation streets and lots is likely. Some storm drains will overflow, and some seawalls and docks will be overtopped. Boaters can expect less clearance under fixed bridges. Motorists should remember that persistent puddles around the times of high tide are almost certain to contain a mix of saltwater. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Portions of the Lower Keys may need to be added to the Coastal Flood Statements by later today or tomorrow.
info.instruction: Do not drive through flooded roadways.
